# Using 'REST Client' plugin for VS Code

@restlUrl = http://localhost:8090

### Health Check - Success (200)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/health-check HTTP/1.1

### Error 404 - Not Found
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/not-found HTTP/1.1

### Error 400 - Bad Request
POST {{restlUrl}}/api/bad-request HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "JAVAN",
    "email": "javan@example.com"
}

### Error 500 - Internal Server Error
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/server-error HTTP/1.1

### Slow Response (1s delay)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/slow-endpoint HTTP/1.1

### Timeout Error (10s delay - will likely timeout)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/timeout HTTP/1.1

### ========================================
### CRUD - Users
### ========================================

### LIST - Get All Users
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/users HTTP/1.1

### READ - Get User by ID (Random Data)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/users/123 HTTP/1.1

### READ - Get User by ID (Another User)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/users/456 HTTP/1.1

### READ - Get User Not Found (ID 999)
GET {{restlUrl}}/api/users/999 HTTP/1.1

### CREATE - Create New User (Success)
POST {{restlUrl}}/api/users HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "João Silva",
    "email": "joao.silva@example.com",
    "cep": "12345678"
}

### CREATE - Create New User (Missing CEP - Should fail with 400)
POST {{restlUrl}}/api/users HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Maria Santos",
    "email": "maria.santos@example.com"
}

### UPDATE - Update User (PUT - Full Update)
PUT {{restlUrl}}/api/users/123 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "João Silva Updated",
    "email": "joao.updated@example.com",
    "cep": "98765432"
}

### UPDATE - Partial Update User (PATCH)
PATCH {{restlUrl}}/api/users/456 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "new.email@example.com"
}

### DELETE - Delete User
DELETE {{restlUrl}}/api/users/789 HTTP/1.1


